## Phase 1 — Backend (`digitalservice`)

### 1. Locale package — `internal/i18n/locale.go` (new)

```go
package i18n

const DefaultLocale = "en"
var SupportedLocales = []string{"en", "mn"}

func IsSupported(locale string) bool { ... }
func Resolve(m map[string]string, locale string) string {
    // m[locale] if present and non-empty, else m[DefaultLocale], else "" (or first value found)
}
func ResolveList(m map[string][]string, locale string) []string {
    // same fallback logic
}
func ResolveFromRequest(c *gin.Context) string {
    // ?lang= query param -> validate against SupportedLocales
    // else parse Accept-Language header, take first supported match
    // else DefaultLocale
}
```
`ResolveFromRequest` is a plain function called at the top of each public handler (not
gin middleware) — only ~6 handlers need it, so a shared router-level middleware isn't
worth the indirection.

### 2. Models — `internal/models/{blog,partner,destination}.go`

Convert to locale maps, keeping non-translatable fields as-is (per decisions above):

- **`Blog`**: `Title`, `Excerpt`, `Content`, `Quote` → `map[string]string`. `Tags` stays
  `[]string` (not free text). `Body []BlogSection` **left untouched** (out of scope).
- **`Partner`**: `Title`, `Description` → `map[string]string`. `Name`, `Tag` stay plain
  strings. `Products []PartnerProduct` **left untouched** (out of scope, per decision).
- **`Destination`**: `Overview`, `Accommodation`, `MealPlan`, `Difficulty` →
  `map[string]string`. `Highlights`, `Activities`, `Inclusions`, `Exclusions` →
  `map[string][]string`. `Name`, `Region`, `BestSeasons`, `Categories`, `Tags` stay as
  today (proper noun / filter-key fields — converting `BestSeasons`/`Categories` would
  break the exact-match filters in `destination_service.go:33-34,39-40`).
  - `ItineraryDay` (`destination.go:20-27`): `Title`, `Description` → `map[string]string`;
    `Activities`, `Meals` → `map[string][]string`. `Day`, `Overnight` — wait, `Overnight`
    is free text too (e.g. "Ger Camp") and was rendered on the frontend as
    "Accommodation" this session — convert it to `map[string]string` as well for
    consistency with `Accommodation`/`MealPlan` at the top level.

### 3. Validation — `internal/service/*_service.go`

**No changes needed.** Research found the only existing validation checks are on
`Slug` (Blog, Destination) and `Partner.Name` (`partner_service.go:59`) — none of these
fields are being converted to locale maps, so no `== ""` check needs to change.

### 4. DTOs — new `internal/dto` package

`BlogResponse`, `PartnerResponse`, `DestinationResponse` (+ nested
`DestinationItineraryDayResponse`) with flat string/[]string fields matching today's
pre-migration shape, and mapper functions:

```go
func ToBlogResponse(b *models.Blog, locale string) BlogResponse
func ToPartnerResponse(p *models.Partner, locale string) PartnerResponse
func ToDestinationResponse(d *models.Destination, locale string) DestinationResponse
```
Each uses `i18n.Resolve`/`i18n.ResolveList` per field. List-response variants
(`ToBlogResponses([]*models.Blog, locale) []BlogResponse`, etc.) for the `List` handlers.

### 5. Wire DTOs into public GET handlers

`internal/handler/{blog,partner,destination}_handler.go` — `List`, `GetBySlug`: resolve
locale via `i18n.ResolveFromRequest(c)`, map to DTO, `response.OK`/`response.List` with
the DTO instead of the raw model. Mechanical — these are today's trivial pass-throughs
per research.

### 6. Add missing admin GET routes (Partner, Destination)

Blog already has `ListAdmin`/`GetByID` wired at `router.go:192-193`, returning raw models
(untouched, per the original plan). **Partner and Destination have no admin GET routes at
all** — needed so the admin edit forms can load full locale-map data. Add, mirroring the
Blog pattern:
- `PartnerHandler.ListAdmin` / `PartnerHandler.GetByID` (new handler methods) +
  `router.go`: `tenantScoped.GET("/admin/partners", ...)`, `GET("/admin/partners/:id", ...)`.
- `DestinationHandler.GetByID` (new; `List` can likely be reused/adapted for
  `ListAdmin` since `DestinationRepo.FindByID` already exists) +
  `router.go`: `tenantScoped.GET("/admin/destinations", ...)`, `GET("/admin/destinations/:id", ...)`.
  Check `PartnerRepo` for an existing `FindByID`/`FindAll`-without-filter equivalent;
  add if missing, following `DestinationRepo`/`BlogRepo`'s existing methods as the
  template.
These return raw models (full locale maps), unauthenticated-tenant-scoped like other
`/admin/*` routes — no DTO involved.

### 7. Create/Update handlers

No code changes — confirmed `ShouldBindJSON`/`bson.M` already accept map-shaped JSON on
write. Per-locale dot-notation PATCH (`"title.mn": "..."`) will work **after** the
migration (step 8) converts existing documents' fields from strings to embedded docs —
note this dependency doesn't require code changes, just migration-before-first-PATCH.

### 8. Migration script — `cmd/migrate-i18n/main.go` (new)

Connects via `MONGO_URI`/`MONGO_DB` (same config as `cmd/api/main.go`), and for each
affected collection (`blogs`, `partners`, `destinations`), for each document, wraps
existing flat string values into `{"en": "<value>"}` for every converted field
(including nested `itinerary[].title`/`description`/`activities`/`meals`/`overnight`),
using `$set` with the already-string values re-written as objects (read doc as
`bson.M`, transform in Go, write back — not a Mongo-side dot-notation `$set`, since the
whole point is the current type doesn't support that yet). Idempotent: skip fields
already shaped as an object. I will write this script but **will not run it** — the user
runs it manually against Atlas when ready.

### 9. `internal/handler/docs/openapi.json`

Manual edit (confirmed hand-authored, not generated) — update the response schemas for
`GET /destinations`, `GET /destinations/:slug`, `GET /blogs`, `GET /blogs/:slug`,
`GET /partners`, `GET /partners/:slug` to the new flat DTO shape, and add the new
`GET /admin/partners`, `GET /admin/partners/:id`, `GET /admin/destinations`,
`GET /admin/destinations/:id` entries (locale-map shape, matching the existing
`GET /admin/blogs` doc entry as a template) plus the new `?lang=` query param.

### Backend verification
- `go build ./...` and `go vet ./...` clean.
- Start the API locally (`cmd/api`), hit `GET /api/v1/destinations?lang=mn` and
  `?lang=en` (and with no `lang` at all) against a migrated doc, confirm flat strings
  resolve correctly with fallback to `en` for missing translations.
- Hit new `GET /api/v1/admin/partners/:id` and `GET /api/v1/admin/destinations/:id`,
  confirm they return full `{"en":..., "mn":...}` maps.
- Confirm existing `POST`/`PUT` admin flows still accept plain object bodies
  (`{"title": {"en": "...", "mn": "..."}}`) end to end.

