## Phase 2 — Admin (`admin`)

### 1. Locale type — `src/lib/types.ts` (or new `src/lib/locale.ts`)
`export type Locale = 'en' | 'mn'`, `export const LOCALES: Locale[] = ['en', 'mn']`,
`export const DEFAULT_LOCALE: Locale = 'en'`.

### 2. `<MultiLangField>` — new `src/components/admin/MultiLangField.tsx`
Built from scratch (research confirmed no existing tab UI to reuse). Locale tabs +
single `<input>`/`<textarea>` swapped per active tab, serializing to one hidden JSON
input — same pattern as `RichTextEditor.tsx`'s `<input type="hidden" name={name}
value={html} readOnly />`, so `actions.ts` needs only `jsonField<Record<Locale,string>>`
(the helper already exists in `tours/actions.ts:27-35`) instead of `String(...)`.
Support a `multiline` prop for textarea vs input, and a `list` mode for
`Highlights`/`Activities`/`Inclusions`/`Exclusions` (`Record<Locale, string>`, still
newline-delimited per locale — the per-locale value is the whole multi-line block, split
into a `string[]` at submit time same as today's `listFieldLines`).

### 3. `<MultiLangRichTextEditor>` — new `src/components/admin/MultiLangRichTextEditor.tsx`
Per user decision: mount one `RichTextEditor`-equivalent Tiptap instance per locale
simultaneously, toggle visibility via CSS (`hidden` class) on the inactive tab's
container, not conditional unmounting — avoids re-init/focus loss. Serializes to one
hidden JSON input (`Record<Locale, string>` of HTML). Used for `Blog.content` and
`Destination.overview`.

### 4. Wire into forms
- **`DestinationForm.tsx`**: `overview` → `<MultiLangRichTextEditor>`. `accommodation`,
  `meal_plan` → `<MultiLangField>`. `highlights`/`activities`/`inclusions`/`exclusions` →
  `<MultiLangField list>`. `name` stays plain `<input>` (per decision). `ItineraryEditor`
  needs its per-day `title`/`description`/`activities`/`meals`/`overnight` fields to
  become locale-aware too — extend `ItineraryDayInput` and its row UI to embed
  `<MultiLangField>` per sub-field (most invasive single change in this phase, since
  `ItineraryEditor` is a repeating-row component).
- **`BlogForm.tsx`**: `title` → `<MultiLangField>`, `excerpt` → `<MultiLangField
  multiline>`, `content` → `<MultiLangRichTextEditor>`. `category`/`tags` unchanged.
- **`PartnerForm.tsx`**: `title` → `<MultiLangField>`, `description` →
  `<MultiLangField multiline>`. `name`, `tag`, `product_name`/`product_description`
  stay plain (per decision — Products excluded from scope).
- **`ReviewForm.tsx`**: `review` → `<MultiLangField multiline>`.

### 5. Form state types & `actions.ts`
Each `bodyFromForm`-equivalent (`tours/actions.ts`, `blog/actions.ts`,
`partners/actions.ts`, `reviews/actions.ts`) swaps the plain-string field reads for
`jsonField<Record<Locale,string>>(formData, '<name>') ?? {}` on the converted fields —
sends the map straight through to `/admin/...`, no reshaping (per original plan, now
mechanically correct given the hidden-JSON-input serialization in step 2/3).

### 6. Data fetching for edit pages
`getDestinationBySlug`/equivalent for Partner and Blog edit pages need to hit the (now
newly added in Phase 1) admin `GET .../:id` endpoints so they receive full locale maps
to pre-fill each tab — confirm `src/lib/data/destinations.ts` (or equivalent) targets
`/admin/destinations/:id` and `/admin/partners/:id`, adding the client calls if the
admin data layer doesn't already have a "get by id" function for Partner (Blog's
already exists per the existing `admin/blogs/:id` route).

### 7. List/table pages
`blog/page.tsx:18`, `partners/page.tsx:17-19`, `tours/page.tsx:18`,
`reviews/page.tsx:22` — each `render: (x) => x.field` becomes
`x.field[DEFAULT_LOCALE] ?? Object.values(x.field)[0] ?? '—'`.

### Admin verification
- `npx tsc --noEmit` clean.
- Preview: create/edit a Destination with both `en` and `mn` overview text (including
  itinerary day fields), confirm the hidden inputs serialize both locales, submit, and
  reload the edit page to confirm both locales round-trip from the backend correctly.
- Confirm list pages don't crash on records that only have `en` (no `mn` key yet,
  pre-migration or partially-translated).

