## Phase 3 — Public frontend (`eandstravelmongolia`)

### 1. `lib/data/*.ts` — thread `locale: Locale` through
`getAllTours`, `getTourBySlug`, `getAllArticles`, `getArticleBySlug`, `getAllPartners`,
`getPartnerBySlug` (and their wrappers `getTours`, `getFeaturedTours`,
`getRelatedTours`, `getArticles`, `getRelatedArticles`) each gain a `locale: Locale`
parameter, forwarded as `{ ...existingParams, lang: locale }` into `apiGet`. `apiGet`
itself (`src/lib/api/client.ts:63`) needs no changes — already takes arbitrary
`searchParams`.

### 2. Page call sites
Every `[locale]/**/page.tsx` already destructures `{ locale }` from `params` — just pass
it into the data calls (`getTourBySlug(slug, locale)`, etc.) at each site research
enumerated. **Two gaps need fixing first**, not just "pass the existing variable":
- `src/app/[locale]/page.tsx` (homepage) currently has no `params` prop at all — add
  `{ params }: { params: Promise<{ locale: string }> }` and `const { locale } =
  await params` like every other page.
- `src/app/api/tours/route.ts`, `src/app/api/tours/[slug]/route.ts`,
  `src/app/api/journal/route.ts`, `src/app/api/journal/[slug]/route.ts`, and
  `src/app/sitemap.ts` have no locale route param in scope (not under `[locale]`) —
  default these to `defaultLocale` (`'en'`) from `src/lib/i18n.ts`, matching the
  backend's own default-locale fallback.

### 3. Types unchanged
Confirmed: `Tour`/`Partner`/`JournalArticle` interfaces stay flat strings — the backend
DTO resolves to a single locale server-side, so the frontend shape is unchanged from
today. No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` sites need changes beyond receiving already-resolved
HTML strings (backend DTO for `overview`/`content` resolves the locale map to one HTML
string before responding — confirmed by the Phase 1 DTO design, not a frontend concern).

### 4. Caching
No extra work — confirmed `apiGet`'s `next: { revalidate: 300 }` caches per full URL, so
`lang=en` vs `lang=mn` are independent cache entries automatically, as long as `lang` is
included in the same `searchParams` object passed to `apiGet` (not appended separately).

### Frontend verification
- `npx tsc --noEmit` clean.
- Preview: visit `/en/tours/<slug>` and `/mn/tours/<slug>` for a tour with both locales
  translated in the admin, confirm overview/itinerary/highlights render the correct
  language on each.
- Confirm a tour with only `en` translated still renders correctly (fallback) under
  `/mn/...`.
- Confirm homepage and journal/partners pages behave the same way.

